# Runner contract

The real runner exists to invoke fetcher scripts **exactly the way the Python runner does**, so existing fetchers run unmodified. Source of truth: [run_fetchers.py](../../../evidence-fetchers/3-run-fetchers/run_fetchers.py).

## Invocation

```
[bash|python3] <script> <profile> <region> <output_dir> /dev/null \
  --profile <profile> --region <region> --output-dir <output_dir> [extra-flags]
```

- CWD = the configured fetcher repo root.
- Env = process env merged with secrets store and per-instance overrides; always set `EVIDENCE_DIR=<output_dir>`.
- `.py` scripts run via `python3`; everything else via `bash`.
- Use `exec.CommandContext`, never `exec.Command`, so cancels and timeouts work.

## Timeouts

- Default `FETCHER_TIMEOUT=300s`.
- Per-fetcher override via `<SCRIPT_NAME>_TIMEOUT`.
- `ssllabs_tls_scan` floor: 3600s.

## AWS pre/post-flight (do not skip)

- **Pre**: `aws sts get-caller-identity --profile <p> [--region <r>]` before any AWS-source fetcher; on failure surface "run `aws sso login --profile <p>`".
- **Post**: parse the produced JSON; if `metadata.account_id == "unknown"` or `metadata.arn == "unknown"`, downgrade exit-0 to FAIL and set `error_reason`.

## Multi-instance

- Discover `AWS_REGION_<N>_*`, `GITLAB_PROJECT_<N>_*`, `CHECKOV_INSTANCE_<N>_*` from env.
- Sanitize resource ids: `/` -> `_`, then strip non-`[A-Za-z0-9_-]`.
- File routing: try exact `<script>` -> strip trailing `_(project|region)_\d+` -> `<script>_<sanitized_resource>` stem. **Never prefix-match for multi-instance** — that bleeds files across projects.

## Cancel & output

- Cancel: SIGTERM, then SIGKILL after 5s. Card status -> `cancelled`.
- Pipe stdout/stderr line-by-line into `OutputMsg`. Cap UI buffer at 400 lines and tee everything to `<output_dir>/<id>/{stdout,stderr}.log`.
